WEBVTT

00:02.770 --> 00:05.159
Previously on "Salem"...

00:07.070 --> 00:09.163
There is not a soul
who can stop me.

00:09.210 --> 00:11.360
ISAAC:
What's become of Mary?
JOHN: She's dead.

00:11.410 --> 00:13.878
For now, we go home...
for her.

00:13.910 --> 00:16.208
BOY: The terror outside
drives refugees into Salem,

00:16.250 --> 00:19.174
where, soon, they all,
including my dear father,

00:19.220 --> 00:23.543
will be but the burning candles
that ignite my inauguration.

00:23.590 --> 00:25.387
You have no idea
what you're up against.

00:25.420 --> 00:28.912
Lead the militia,
and I'll clear your name.

00:28.960 --> 00:31.520
SEBASTIAN: My sister harbors
a great danger to you, Lord --

00:31.560 --> 00:32.822
Cotton Mather.

00:32.860 --> 00:35.021
_ ANN_E:
(Sing-song vorce) Cotton.

00:35.060 --> 00:36.869
Aah!
Have no fear.

00:36.900 --> 00:38.219
It's just you
and me...

00:38.270 --> 00:39.931
(rat squeaking)
...and baby makes three.

00:39.970 --> 00:42.564
PETRUS: What you
and the Essex witches have done

00:42.610 --> 00:44.908
by bringing back
the Devil himself --

00:44.940 --> 00:46.498
now, see what I see.

00:46.540 --> 00:50.670
You and Mary Sibley
gave the Devil the earth.

00:50.710 --> 00:54.669
Now you and Mary Sibley
have got to take it back.

00:54.720 --> 00:56.347
MERCY:
Who do we have here?

00:56.390 --> 00:58.210
A little lost bird
for my little nest?

00:58.250 --> 01:01.686
You _will never have to_
deal With your uncle again.

01:01.720 --> 01:02.926
JOHN:
This is where you work?

01:02.960 --> 01:04.188
ISAAC: Knockers Hole.

01:04.230 --> 01:05.879
Does anybody know
this man's name?

01:05.930 --> 01:08.353
Finally, brother,
you are here.

01:08.400 --> 01:10.868
TITUBA: We all know that
this is our only chance.

01:10.900 --> 01:12.128
Raise the dead,

01:12.170 --> 01:14.297
and you never know
what you raise.

01:14.340 --> 01:16.535
(Mary screeches)

01:16.570 --> 01:18.731
(breathing heavily)

01:20.080 --> 01:22.207
(breathing heavily)

01:22.250 --> 01:24.241
John.

01:24.280 --> 01:26.043
No!

01:26.080 --> 01:30.141
(panﬁng)

01:31.750 --> 01:34.787
John!

01:34.820 --> 01:36.822
John?

01:36.860 --> 01:38.589
John!

01:38.630 --> 01:40.598
John, where are you?

01:40.630 --> 01:43.428
I'm here, John.

01:43.470 --> 01:45.927
Where is he?

01:45.970 --> 01:48.131
(panﬁng)

01:55.840 --> 01:57.774
No!
I'm sorry, Sister.

01:57.810 --> 02:00.449
No,
get out of my way!

02:00.480 --> 02:02.516
(panﬁng)

02:11.460 --> 02:13.894
(growling, shouting)

02:18.870 --> 02:20.792
Shh, Shh.

02:20.840 --> 02:23.308
(panﬁng)

02:26.180 --> 02:30.674
What have you done
to me now, Queen of Bitches?

02:30.710 --> 02:34.714
Only ripped your soul
through the wall of silence,

02:34.750 --> 02:37.184
cursed you back to life,

02:37.220 --> 02:42.180
and trapped you forever
in the home of all your tears.

02:42.230 --> 02:46.223
Run as far and as fast
as you may, Mary Sibley.

02:46.260 --> 02:47.921
You can never escape Salem.

02:50.270 --> 02:54.297
ESSEX ELDER: You are resurrected
by the very life force

02:54.340 --> 02:56.865
of the primordial tree.

02:56.910 --> 03:00.732
Now you are forever bound
to the realm of its roots --

03:00.780 --> 03:02.133
to Salem.

03:02.180 --> 03:05.149
Is this now
to be my personal Hell?

03:05.180 --> 03:08.513
Have you brought me back
and staked my soul

03:08.550 --> 03:10.643
to Salem
just to watch me suffer?

03:10.690 --> 03:12.351
No, child.

03:12.390 --> 03:15.757
'Tis no punishment,
but a gift.

03:15.790 --> 03:20.750
You've been given the chance
to undo all your crimes.

03:20.800 --> 03:22.927
My crimes?

03:22.970 --> 03:26.758
Why, you lying,
filthy whore!

03:26.800 --> 03:30.065
My crimes
are your crimes.

03:30.110 --> 03:33.375
We are all responsible.

03:33.410 --> 03:37.608
Together, we turned the
witch hunt against the hunters.

03:37.650 --> 03:40.414
And we sought justice
for all our sisters

03:40.450 --> 03:43.010
burned and hanged
in the old country.

03:43.050 --> 03:45.348
But the devil lied,

03:45.390 --> 03:48.780
and he delivers justice
only for himself

03:48.820 --> 03:51.618
and death or slavery
for all others.

03:51.660 --> 03:54.527
It is true.
I have seen it.

03:54.560 --> 03:56.562
The devil
we led you to birth

03:56.600 --> 03:59.262
will enslave this land
unless we stop hIm.

03:59.300 --> 04:00.562
We must --
We? We?!

04:00.600 --> 04:01.794
No.

04:01.840 --> 04:03.262
No, if you want to undo
all of this,

04:03.310 --> 04:05.699
then you will have
to undo it without me!

04:05.740 --> 04:07.708
You are the only one

04:07.740 --> 04:11.141
in Heaven or Earth
who can destroy him.

04:11.180 --> 04:14.274
You and he
were of one body.

04:14.320 --> 04:16.641
You knitted his flesh
in your womb.

04:16.690 --> 04:20.581
I already saved the one person
in this world I loved.

04:20.620 --> 04:22.087
Well,
I'm sorry to tell you,

04:22.120 --> 04:25.556
but your sacrifice accomplished
precisely nothing --

04:25.590 --> 04:29.299
saved no one,
least of all John Alden.

04:29.330 --> 04:33.039
**

04:44.780 --> 04:47.749
(gasps)

04:47.780 --> 04:50.442
If you want to save
the life of your love,

04:50.490 --> 04:53.653
it is not enough
to kill yourself.

04:53.690 --> 04:55.851
You must kill your son.

05:00.960 --> 05:03.394
("Cupid Carries A Gun" plays)

05:08.470 --> 05:11.530
* Pound me the witch drums

05:11.570 --> 05:12.969
* The witch drums

05:13.010 --> 05:16.844
* Pound me the witch drums

05:16.880 --> 05:19.474
* Pound me the witch drums

05:19.520 --> 05:21.215
* The witch drums

05:21.250 --> 05:23.480
* Better pray for hell

05:23.520 --> 05:29.459
* Not hallelujah

05:29.490 --> 05:32.493
**

05:45.740 --> 05:48.208
You stupid waste
of flesh and blood.

05:48.240 --> 05:50.674
I didn't kill Mary.
I saved her.

05:50.710 --> 05:53.144
(both panting)

05:53.180 --> 05:54.716
What --

05:54.750 --> 05:57.913
by bleeding her dry through
a goddamn hole in her neck?

05:57.950 --> 05:59.759
You didn't deserve it.

05:59.790 --> 06:01.314
What?

06:01.360 --> 06:03.419
I left her
blood enough to survive,

06:03.460 --> 06:07.021
to be free of Salem --
free of me, even.

06:07.060 --> 06:10.564
She must have found you clinging
to your pathetic life

06:10.600 --> 06:13.831
and wasted her last precious
life's blood to save you.

06:13.870 --> 06:17.101
You killed her,
Captain,

06:17.140 --> 06:20.507
as if
you cut her throat.

06:20.540 --> 06:22.679
You should have had
the decency

06:22.710 --> 06:24.871
to let _them _
hang you this morning.

06:24.910 --> 06:26.138
HATHORNE: Gentlemen!

06:27.480 --> 06:29.846
Gentlemen, please!

06:29.890 --> 06:35.681
Salem's survival rests
on the shoulders of two men.

06:35.720 --> 06:37.426
And I can't afford
either of you

06:37.460 --> 06:40.429
to reduce that number
by half.

06:40.460 --> 06:44.294
Captain Alden,
you promised me trained troops.

06:44.330 --> 06:45.558
We need them.

06:45.600 --> 06:48.569
The enemy may be
at our very gates.

06:48.600 --> 06:52.229
Not_ all enemies
are In the woods.

06:52.270 --> 06:55.603
**

06:58.680 --> 07:01.148
(indistinct conversations)

07:03.520 --> 07:07.479
So, this is
what it all comes to.

07:07.520 --> 07:11.627
The great hope of generations
of Cottons and Mathers,

07:11.660 --> 07:17.860
reduced to a hand puppet
of Witches and demon lovers.

07:19.700 --> 07:23.568
(trembling)

07:23.610 --> 07:25.237
Please.

07:25.270 --> 07:26.476
Let me.

07:26.510 --> 07:28.171
No.

07:28.210 --> 07:32.306
I cannot -- I will not --
allow you destroy yourself,

07:32.350 --> 07:35.319
nor will I allow them
to destroy you.

07:35.350 --> 07:37.318
(sighs)

07:37.350 --> 07:42.151
Time will show us the way
if you will but let it.

07:42.190 --> 07:44.681
Our true marriage
has not yet begun.

07:44.730 --> 07:47.221
The children
we might have --

07:51.730 --> 07:54.130
If you wish me
to endure, I need a drink.

07:54.170 --> 07:57.662
And drown poor Brown Jenkins?
I think not.

08:05.010 --> 08:10.687
You do not understand _
the danger you -- we all are In.

08:10.720 --> 08:14.315
The power that now rules Salem
is far greater than mine

08:14.360 --> 08:19.059
and utterly evil
in its intent.

08:19.090 --> 08:23.322
You must trust that all I do,
I do for you --

08:23.370 --> 08:26.498
for your protection,
our future.

08:26.540 --> 08:30.135
I am in your hands.

08:30.170 --> 08:32.809
Not hers, but in the hands
of the Dark Lord.

08:32.840 --> 08:34.239
Lay a finger on Cotton

08:34.280 --> 08:35.679
and I will paint these walls
with your insides.

08:35.710 --> 08:37.701
That boy be damned.

08:37.750 --> 08:39.911
Our little master
simply has use of your husband.

08:39.950 --> 08:42.680
The people are afraid.

08:42.720 --> 08:45.041
They need to hear from the great
Reverend Cotton Mather.

08:45.090 --> 08:47.354
What does the Devil care
If people are afraid?

08:47.390 --> 08:49.722
Even
the dimmest butcher knows

08:49.760 --> 08:52.081
not to let the cow see
the blow that is coming.

08:52.130 --> 08:55.497
Fear taints the meat.

08:55.530 --> 08:59.068
I will not serve him.

08:59.100 --> 09:01.864
I'd rather die instead.

09:01.900 --> 09:05.438
I would do so in an instant
were I allowed.

09:05.470 --> 09:07.734
SEBASTIAN:
I'm not sure I believe you.

09:07.780 --> 09:10.544
I think you and I
are more alike than that.

09:10.580 --> 09:13.413
And we both know
that martyrdom is for fools

09:13.450 --> 09:15.179
who dream
of a glorious death

09:15.220 --> 09:17.586
_ that will ensure
their memory lives forever.

09:17.620 --> 09:21.386
Personally, I'd prefer
it were not my memory

09:21.420 --> 09:23.581
that lives forever,
but me.

09:23.630 --> 09:27.157
And I think deep down,
you are the same.

09:32.840 --> 09:37.265
IfI am wrong and you do wish
to martyr yourself,

09:37.310 --> 09:40.529
you will have that chance
in the meeting house.

09:40.580 --> 09:42.741
Say the wrong thing,
and you will die.

09:42.780 --> 09:45.704
Say the right thing,
and you will live.

09:45.750 --> 09:49.242
Either way,
the cattle shall still be eaten.

09:49.280 --> 09:52.147
_ Just serve him
in the most minimal of ways,

09:52.190 --> 09:53.418
and he will allow you
and my sister

09:53.460 --> 09:55.815
to live
happily ever after.

09:55.860 --> 09:58.579
This is our chance.

10:00.360 --> 10:02.328
Chance?
(door closes)

10:02.360 --> 10:03.793
(scoffs)

10:03.830 --> 10:06.958
A chance to destroy
everything I've lived for.

10:07.000 --> 10:08.888
You would have me be
a Judas Goat

10:08.940 --> 10:10.965
and lead my own people
to slaughter.

10:11.010 --> 10:14.002
No,
I would have you live.

10:19.210 --> 10:23.089
DINLEY: Most men die
as they are born -- in agony,

10:23.120 --> 10:28.012
but this man's agony
must have been exceptional.

10:28.060 --> 10:31.223
Every bone in his body...

10:34.200 --> 10:35.929
...has been crushed.

10:35.960 --> 10:37.860
A suspicious death,
then?

10:37.900 --> 10:41.961
Well, in Knockers Hole,
all deaths are suspicious.

10:42.000 --> 10:43.865
Why care
about this one?

10:43.910 --> 10:47.334
Every man --
even a poor man,

10:47.380 --> 10:50.872
even a bad man --
deserves dignity in death.

10:50.910 --> 10:52.775
I think dignity begins
with a name.

10:52.820 --> 10:54.708
That I could give you.

10:54.750 --> 10:57.184
Stitched him up
more than once.

10:57.220 --> 11:03.352
Nick Land -- a gambler,
a thief, a drunkard, and pimp.

11:03.390 --> 11:05.358
Did he have any family?

11:05.390 --> 11:06.857
Alice.

11:06.900 --> 11:09.289
I can assure you
she won't be shedding any tears.

11:09.330 --> 11:10.820
Why not?

11:10.870 --> 11:15.398
I said that he was a pimp --
her pimp.

11:20.410 --> 11:22.605
(sighing)

11:28.020 --> 11:31.683
I have better use
for those precious hands.

11:33.620 --> 11:35.258
Mary!

11:38.360 --> 11:40.328
No, it cannot be.

11:40.360 --> 11:42.419
But it is,
my love.

11:42.460 --> 11:44.189
How?

11:44.230 --> 11:47.393
I buried you.

11:47.440 --> 11:51.206
**

11:55.280 --> 11:57.840
I've seen
the other side, John.

11:57.880 --> 12:00.178
There's no life there,
no love.

12:00.220 --> 12:03.940
_ All we have
is here and now.

12:05.490 --> 12:07.412
Fine,
then come away.

12:07.460 --> 12:09.553
We can escape
before anyone's even awake.

12:09.590 --> 12:11.421
John,
I can never leave this place.

12:11.460 --> 12:14.190
The magic that raised me
traps me here.

12:14.230 --> 12:17.222
I must spend
the rest of my life in Salem.

12:17.270 --> 12:19.625
Whatever you must do,
we do it together.

12:19.670 --> 12:22.366
Tell me.

12:22.400 --> 12:24.038
There will be time
to talk of that.

12:24.070 --> 12:28.302
For now,
it is not talk I need.

12:28.340 --> 12:29.739
John.

12:29.780 --> 12:32.374
I've swum beyond
the wall of sleep.

12:32.410 --> 12:36.073
I've been alive and dead
and then alive again.

12:36.120 --> 12:41.319
And right now, all I want
is to feel you inside me.

12:41.360 --> 12:43.828
Can you do that?

12:43.860 --> 12:45.851
(both breathing heavily)

12:50.930 --> 12:55.162
Let _the Devil rule _
the world just one more night.

12:55.200 --> 12:57.361
(both breathing heavily)

13:00.980 --> 13:03.005
(both moaning)

13:03.050 --> 13:06.144
**

13:15.390 --> 13:18.553
**

13:19.560 --> 13:22.427
Where are you going?

13:22.460 --> 13:25.759
Where only I can go.

13:25.800 --> 13:27.131
No.

13:27.170 --> 13:28.694
Not alone.

13:28.740 --> 13:30.708
You can't help me, John.

13:30.740 --> 13:32.162
I made that boy's body.

13:32.210 --> 13:33.632
Only I can unmake him.

13:33.680 --> 13:35.705
You said you'd tell me all,
that there'd be time.

13:35.740 --> 13:38.470
I lied.

13:38.510 --> 13:42.219
There's no time --
no time at all.

13:42.250 --> 13:47.051
IfI succeed, then we'll have
all the time in the world.

13:47.090 --> 13:51.026
IfI fail...

13:51.060 --> 13:53.449
then at least
I felt your love in me

13:53.500 --> 13:55.559
once
before the darkness fell.

13:58.030 --> 13:59.793
I'm
5
0
